OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWife-killer faces UK's     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffirst public parole hearing
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The parole hearing of a man who killed 
OL,6, his wife but never revealed where her  
OL,7, body was will be the first in UK       
OL,8, history to be heard in public.         
OL,10,FRussell Causley, now 79, murdered      
OL,11,FCarole Packman in Bournemouth in 1985. 
OL,13,FCausley was only brought to justice a  
OL,14,Fdecade later after he made a botched   
OL,15,Fattempt to fake his own death as part  
OL,16,Fof an elaborate insurance fraud.       
OL,18,FThe Parole Board confirmed Causley     
OL,19,Fwould now argue for his release during 
OL,20,Fa hearing set to take place in October.
